00:00:50,451 --> 00:00:52,784
narrator: a hot rod is a normal car   

4
00:00:52,786 --> 00:00:54,453
that's been radically modified 

5
00:00:54,455 --> 00:00:56,721
to look snazzier and drive faster.       

6
00:00:56,723 --> 00:00:59,725
some amateur mechanics tinker away at building one  

7
00:00:59,727 --> 00:01:00,792
in their garage,        

8
00:01:00,794 --> 00:01:03,195
while other car buffs custom-order one        

9
00:01:03,197 --> 00:01:04,930
from a specialty auto shop.  

10
00:01:04,932 --> 00:01:08,333
either way, hot-rod lovers are driven by their passion  

11
00:01:08,335 --> 00:01:10,536
for these mean machines.    

12
00:01:14,608 --> 00:01:17,009
hot rods are customized inside and out.        

13
00:01:17,011 --> 00:01:19,277
the classic cars they start out as       

14
00:01:19,279 --> 00:01:21,012
are pretty scarce these days, 

15
00:01:21,014 --> 00:01:24,283
so specialty shops now design and build hot-rod bodies    

16
00:01:24,285 --> 00:01:25,350
from scratch,         

17
00:01:25,352 --> 00:01:28,353
using state-of-the-art technologies.         

18
00:01:28,355 --> 00:01:32,290
it all starts with curved steel rails 15 feet long    

19
00:01:32,292 --> 00:01:34,893
that form the basis of the chassis.        

20
00:01:34,895 --> 00:01:40,165
every 12 inches, workers weld the rails to the car's frame. 

21
00:01:40,167 --> 00:01:44,403
next they position cross members
to reinforce the frame.    

22
00:01:46,540 --> 00:01:49,107
with utmost concern for quality control,      

23
00:01:49,109 --> 00:01:52,310
they'll assemble and install by hand the transmission,   

24
00:01:52,312 --> 00:01:54,846
the suspension, and the shock absorbers    

25
00:01:54,848 --> 00:01:57,649
and weld those precisely aligned
cross members         

26
00:01:57,651 --> 00:02:00,085
to the curved rails.      

27
00:02:03,723 --> 00:02:07,593
elsewhere, someone polishes the stainless-steel wings,   

28
00:02:07,595 --> 00:02:09,327
which have been laser cut.   

29
00:02:09,329 --> 00:02:12,764
these wings make up the    
hot rod's signature front grill.

30
00:02:20,608 --> 00:02:22,941
mounting the disc brakes onto such a high-end machine  

31
00:02:22,943 --> 00:02:25,143
takes specialists.       

32
00:02:25,145 --> 00:02:28,113
first, they screw the spindles to the suspension arm...    

33
00:02:30,284 --> 00:02:32,784
...then grease the ball-bearing mechanism... 

34
00:02:34,488 --> 00:02:37,890
...and finally block the disc brake with a cotter pin    

35
00:02:37,892 --> 00:02:39,958
to fasten the pieces together. 

36
00:02:39,960 --> 00:02:43,228
the brake system has four calipers, one per wheel.    

37
00:02:43,230 --> 00:02:46,564
each one holds two brackets called the brake shoes.    

38
00:02:46,566 --> 00:02:48,900
they close down on the brake disc       

39
00:02:48,902 --> 00:02:51,703
to slow down and stop the wheel's rotation. 

40
00:02:51,705 --> 00:02:55,040
a couple of slide pins lock the caliper into place.  

41
00:02:55,042 --> 00:02:57,042
brake shoes are prone to wear, 

42
00:02:57,044 --> 00:03:01,980
so their alignment and oiling must be perfect.        

43
00:03:01,982 --> 00:03:04,649
time has come to install a hydraulic device       

44
00:03:04,651 --> 00:03:07,586
that reacts to the steering wheel's movement,       

45
00:03:07,588 --> 00:03:11,156
directing the tie rods to turn the front wheels accordingly.  

46
00:03:12,459 --> 00:03:13,659
a pneumatic tool is used    

47
00:03:13,661 --> 00:03:16,061
to affix the pinion of the steering mechanism.   

48
00:03:19,600 --> 00:03:25,470
at every step, workers check and double-check each part.   

49
00:03:25,472 --> 00:03:27,138
using a jack,         

50
00:03:27,140 --> 00:03:29,741
they lift the differential housing into position.     

51
00:03:29,743 --> 00:03:32,144
it anchors the rear wheels' propulsion system       

52
00:03:32,146 --> 00:03:33,612
to the car's frame.      

53
00:03:33,614 --> 00:03:38,617
they attach the suspension arms
to the axles at an angle.   

54
00:03:38,619 --> 00:03:42,220
meanwhile, a painter sprays a coat of resin gel      

55
00:03:42,222 --> 00:03:43,821
on the plastic molds      

56
00:03:43,823 --> 00:03:46,691
with which they make the car's fiberglass body parts.     

57
00:03:46,693 --> 00:03:48,426
the gel coating eases extraction

58
00:03:48,428 --> 00:03:51,696
and gives the fiberglass a high-gloss finish.      

59
00:03:51,698 --> 00:03:53,098
to mold the parts,       

60
00:03:53,100 --> 00:03:56,100
a worker spreads resin on fiberglass cloth.      

61
00:03:56,102 --> 00:03:59,504
they call this step "wetting the fiberglass map." 

62
00:03:59,506 --> 00:04:03,642
they lay the map on the mold --
in this case, on a door mold --

63
00:04:03,644 --> 00:04:07,646
then with a roller, carefully press out all the air bubbles. 

64
00:04:07,648 --> 00:04:09,314
it takes about 40 minutes   

65
00:04:09,316 --> 00:04:12,116
for the resin-impregnated map to solidify.          

66
00:04:12,118 --> 00:04:15,186
extracting the body part is a tricky procedure.     

67
00:04:15,188 --> 00:04:18,790
they hammer wood wedges in between the hardened fiberglass

68
00:04:18,792 --> 00:04:21,193
in the mold.          

69
00:04:21,195 --> 00:04:24,128
it's crucial to angle the wedge
just right.          

70
00:04:24,130 --> 00:04:26,465
otherwise, the mold may collapse.     

71
00:04:26,467 --> 00:04:29,134
it typically takes about 25 molded parts     

72
00:04:29,136 --> 00:04:31,536
to make up a complete hot-rod body.    

73
00:04:31,538 --> 00:04:35,006
after three week's work, final assembly begins.     

74
00:04:35,008 --> 00:04:37,876
after the back panels comes the front,        

75
00:04:37,878 --> 00:04:40,011
otherwise known as the nose.  

76
00:04:40,013 --> 00:04:43,882
next come the fenders, then the stylish running board.

77
00:04:43,884 --> 00:04:47,352
and no hot rod is complete without its signature grill.  

78
00:04:47,354 --> 00:04:50,154
the windshield frame helps support the roof,    

79
00:04:50,156 --> 00:04:53,024
or "carson top" in hot-rod lingo.       

80
00:04:53,026 --> 00:04:57,129
the front hood completes this '37-ford-inspired body.  

81
00:04:58,565 --> 00:05:00,899
it ships out without a paint job.      

82
00:05:00,901 --> 00:05:04,903
that's because customization is
everything in the hot-rod biz. 

83
00:05:04,905 --> 00:05:07,572
the buyer decides how to finish the car     

84
00:05:07,574 --> 00:05:10,575
by choosing, for example, this retro dashboard      

85
00:05:10,577 --> 00:05:14,246
designed to blend spectacularly
with the rest of the car.   

86
00:05:17,718 --> 00:05:19,917
even car junkies can be forgiven

87
00:05:19,919 --> 00:05:21,986
for struggling to keep up to speed      

88
00:05:21,988 --> 00:05:25,057
with the ever-growing     
customization options out there.

89
00:05:26,994 --> 00:05:31,663
from the engine to the rims to the seats to the chrome -- 

90
00:05:31,665 --> 00:05:34,399
when it comes to customizing your hot rod,  

91
00:05:34,401 --> 00:05:36,735
you're in the driver's seat.  

